history.content:
As your undergraduate years wind down to completion, you may be finding yourself asking, what comes next? Whether you want to continue your education by pursuing a graduate degree or want to put your skills to use by jumping immediately into the workforce post-graduation, the possible career options available in the tech industry are immense and each one has its respective pros and cons, but which one is right for you?

Hear from Berkeley Theta Tau alumni that majored in EECS, CS, MSE, BioE, and ChemE about their experience in grad school and working in industry along with the benefits of each. Bring a copy of your resume for feedback via email, and come out to talk with alumni about their careers and how they've found success so far.

Find more info on the facebook event here, and we're looking forward to seeing you there!
history.subject: Industry vs Grad School Panel
